docs.lead_paragraph: Have you enough to do, good friend! Then do it, and be thankful that you have. We stand at the opening of an avenue through which people pour their wants upon the world, and we know something of what "wants" are. Some want money. And such can certainly get it, by paying for it. Some want land; that, money will always buy.

headline.main: SUMMER LETTERS.; CANADA.--No. V. Some Days in Canada.

docs.lead_paragraph: The harbor of Quebec is doubtless one the finest on the continent. There is ample room for many miles of wharves, and space to float an Immense quantity of timber, which is its great stagle. The whole British navy might ride here in safety, sheltered from northeasters by the Isle of Orleans; yet at a distance of seven hundred miles, river and gulf, from the open Atlantis.

headline.main: PHILADELPHIA.; Health of the City--Crowded Hotels--Travel to New-York--Money Affairs--Philadelphia Sympathy--Another Murder--Killed Himself--Political Affairs--Markets, &c.

docs.lead_paragraph: The weather is delightful, the thermometer at 2 o'clock, at the Bulletin office, being at 79[degrees]. By the Health Report I see we had four deaths by yellow fever last week. This is the first time the yellow fever has been officially reported, though it has been with us for some time. The city was never more healthy than at present, and all fears of being, visited with an epidemic have vanished.
